1:09:44.281 --> 1:09:47.148
He has more important
things to worry about,

1:09:47.150 --> 1:09:48.516
Like keeping
coal valley safe.

1:09:49.818 --> 1:09:52.420
Or getting thrown out
of drinking establishments.

1:09:52.422 --> 1:09:54.022
-[drops fork]
-[conversations halt]

1:09:56.759 --> 1:09:59.093
Who was thrown out
of a drinking establishment?

1:09:59.095 --> 1:10:01.095
[julie]:
Jack's brother, tom.

1:10:01.097 --> 1:10:02.463
Who's every bit
as good-looking

1:10:02.465 --> 1:10:03.698
As his dashing
older brother.

1:10:04.934 --> 1:10:06.434
How is it
that you're acquainted

1:10:06.436 --> 1:10:08.136
With this "tom" person,
young lady?

1:10:09.405 --> 1:10:11.573
He landed at my feet
this afternoon.

1:10:14.243 --> 1:10:15.476
Well, literally.

1:10:16.779 --> 1:10:18.079
[agatha]: Well!

1:10:18.081 --> 1:10:19.414
This is much more
entertaining

1:10:19.416 --> 1:10:20.982
Than talking
about polo.

1:10:20.984 --> 1:10:22.684
-[jack chuckles]
-tell me.

1:10:22.686 --> 1:10:24.619
Do you make a habit
of drinking, constable thornton?

1:10:24.621 --> 1:10:26.421
No. No, I don't, mrs. Thatcher.

1:10:26.423 --> 1:10:28.223
Certainly
not on the job.

1:10:29.692 --> 1:10:32.493
W-- or really
much at all.

1:10:34.496 --> 1:10:35.964
Or ever.

1:10:35.966 --> 1:10:38.099
Except maybe at dinner.

1:10:40.035 --> 1:10:43.104
Perhaps it's
time for dessert.

1:10:43.106 --> 1:10:44.239
That's an excellent
idea, aunt agatha.

1:10:45.808 --> 1:10:46.874
Tell me, constable.

1:10:46.876 --> 1:10:48.810
What do you think
of peach melba?

1:10:48.812 --> 1:10:51.346
I'm sorry, who?

1:10:54.516 --> 1:10:57.051
It's ice cream.
With peach sauce.

1:10:58.554 --> 1:10:59.821
I know.

1:10:59.823 --> 1:11:01.456
I was just making a joke.

1:11:01.458 --> 1:11:03.224
[others laughing]

1:11:11.667 --> 1:11:12.900
Your mountie has

1:11:12.902 --> 1:11:14.902
A very nice sense
of humor, my dear.

1:11:14.904 --> 1:11:18.072
He isn't "my" mountie,
aunt agatha.

1:11:18.074 --> 1:11:20.074
Isn't he?

1:11:23.245 --> 1:11:25.446
[â™ª]

1:11:28.584 --> 1:11:31.319
[charles and elizabeth
playing the piano]

1:11:35.024 --> 1:11:37.959
[â™ª]

1:11:45.601 --> 1:11:48.169
[elizabeth giggling
as they continue to play]

1:11:58.113 --> 1:12:00.214
[charles and elizabeth chuckling
as they play]

1:12:00.216 --> 1:12:02.283
I've forgotten
how it goes.

1:12:02.285 --> 1:12:05.119
You're still
better at it than me.

1:12:05.121 --> 1:12:08.356
Let's try it again?

1:12:08.358 --> 1:12:10.358
[they begin playing]

1:12:11.560 --> 1:12:13.528
[â™ª]

1:12:21.704 --> 1:12:23.971
[elizabeth chuckling]

1:12:25.874 --> 1:12:27.775
[â™ª]

1:12:27.777 --> 1:12:29.043
They're having such
a good time together,

1:12:29.045 --> 1:12:30.712
Aren't they?

1:12:30.714 --> 1:12:31.979
I've heard
they've been friends

1:12:31.981 --> 1:12:33.481
For a very long time.

1:12:33.483 --> 1:12:36.017
Charles and elizabeth
have a lot in common.

1:12:37.319 --> 1:12:39.287
They took lessons
from the same teachers,

1:12:39.289 --> 1:12:41.656
Shared the same friends,
skinned their knees.

1:12:41.658 --> 1:12:43.558
[both laughing]

1:12:43.560 --> 1:12:46.227
It's a bond that has
stood the test of time.

1:12:46.229 --> 1:12:48.096
Sometimes, what
people have in common

1:12:48.098 --> 1:12:50.331
Are the things
they feel inside.

1:12:50.333 --> 1:12:52.567
A shared spirit.

1:12:53.969 --> 1:12:56.504
Elizabeth is
spirited, all right.

1:12:56.506 --> 1:12:59.440
That's what I like
most about her, sir.

1:12:59.442 --> 1:13:02.143
Sometimes,
I think...

1:13:03.312 --> 1:13:05.179
She doesn't quite
know who she is yet.

1:13:05.181 --> 1:13:06.914
She has a tendency
to follow her heart

1:13:06.916 --> 1:13:09.350
Instead of her head.

1:13:09.352 --> 1:13:11.152
She most likely will
wake up to it one day,

1:13:11.154 --> 1:13:13.988
And I would hate
to see her

1:13:13.990 --> 1:13:16.991
Pass up the life
she so dearly deserves.

1:13:18.160 --> 1:13:19.761
[both laughing
as they stop playing]

1:13:19.763 --> 1:13:21.763
[others clapping]

1:13:23.599 --> 1:13:26.834
I don't think you need
to worry about that, sir.

1:13:26.836 --> 1:13:28.836
If she follows
her heart,

1:13:28.838 --> 1:13:31.072
I'm sure
she'll be just fine.

1:13:32.975 --> 1:13:34.942
[both laughing]

1:13:40.716 --> 1:13:43.317
[lively piano plays]

1:13:43.319 --> 1:13:45.520
[â™ª]

1:13:50.726 --> 1:13:53.094
[all applauding]

1:13:58.467 --> 1:14:01.402
Wow! You play
as pretty as you look.

1:14:01.404 --> 1:14:03.704
Oh! Well,
you talk even prettier.

1:14:03.706 --> 1:14:05.706
Yes, I do!

1:14:05.708 --> 1:14:07.809
You know what this town needs?

1:14:07.811 --> 1:14:09.710
Aside from a sawmill?

1:14:09.712 --> 1:14:11.746
Oh, I have a feeling
you're going to tell me.

1:14:11.748 --> 1:14:13.047
A theater.

1:14:13.049 --> 1:14:14.048
Theater?

1:14:14.050 --> 1:14:15.349
Mm.

1:14:15.351 --> 1:14:16.984
Why would you need a theater?

1:14:16.986 --> 1:14:19.987
Because I have played
on the "great white way"

1:14:19.989 --> 1:14:21.722
Of broadway
in new york city,

1:14:21.724 --> 1:14:23.524
And...

1:14:23.526 --> 1:14:26.060
Well, it would be a shame
to put my talent to waste.

1:14:26.062 --> 1:14:28.729
Ahh! So you're an actress?

1:14:28.731 --> 1:14:31.065
I was the lead in
<i>45 minutes to broadway.</i>

1:14:31.067 --> 1:14:33.868
Well, I thought you said
you were <i>on</i> broadway,

1:14:33.870 --> 1:14:35.837
Not 45 minutes away.

1:14:35.839 --> 1:14:38.105
Mm... [laughs]

1:14:38.107 --> 1:14:40.608
I see I have
a little educating to do.

1:14:43.011 --> 1:14:43.945
[spoon clinking glass]

1:14:43.947 --> 1:14:45.346
Ahem!

1:14:45.348 --> 1:14:49.951
Since we are no longer
going to be "coal" people,

1:14:49.953 --> 1:14:52.019
And with mr. Coulter
bringing us

1:14:52.021 --> 1:14:54.021
New life
and new hope--

1:14:54.023 --> 1:14:55.857
[man]:
Hear, hear!

1:14:55.859 --> 1:14:58.593
As mayor, I think
we should consider changing

1:14:58.595 --> 1:15:01.095
The name
of our fine town.

1:15:01.097 --> 1:15:04.198
And I'm open for suggestions!

1:15:04.200 --> 1:15:07.068
[buzzing chatter rises]

1:15:07.070 --> 1:15:09.270
[â™ª]

1:15:12.207 --> 1:15:14.442
Please tell me
you're not running off

1:15:14.444 --> 1:15:16.577
Before I get a chance
to see you again.

1:15:16.579 --> 1:15:18.279
I don't think I'll be able
to stay more than a few days.

1:15:18.281 --> 1:15:19.413
She's not
going anywhere

1:15:19.415 --> 1:15:20.481
Until we're sure

1:15:20.483 --> 1:15:21.549
Her mother
is fully recovered.

1:15:21.551 --> 1:15:22.650
Oh, william.

1:15:22.652 --> 1:15:24.051
You make it
seem like an invalid.

1:15:24.053 --> 1:15:26.554
I'm under dr. Clement's care,

1:15:26.556 --> 1:15:29.423
And I'm sure I'll be back
to my old self in no time.

1:15:29.425 --> 1:15:32.460
Then... Until
we meet again?

1:15:32.462 --> 1:15:34.328
Until then.

1:15:34.330 --> 1:15:36.397
Jack, it was so good
to see you.

1:15:36.399 --> 1:15:38.366
You, too, julie.

1:15:39.635 --> 1:15:41.669
Thank you
for inviting me.

1:15:41.671 --> 1:15:43.070
I hope
you had a good time.

1:15:43.072 --> 1:15:44.338
What's important

1:15:44.340 --> 1:15:46.107
Is that you're home
with your family.

1:15:46.109 --> 1:15:48.142
I'm at home
in coal valley, too.

1:15:48.144 --> 1:15:49.343
Constable,

1:15:49.345 --> 1:15:50.978
I trust you had
a pleasant evening?

1:15:50.980 --> 1:15:52.513
Very much.
Thank you, sir.

1:15:52.515 --> 1:15:53.748
Will we be
seeing you again?

1:15:53.750 --> 1:15:55.082
No.

1:15:55.084 --> 1:15:57.251
No, I'm leaving hamilton
in the morning.

1:15:59.454 --> 1:16:01.489
That seems kind of sudden.

1:16:01.491 --> 1:16:04.959
Well, you're safe
and settled with your family,

1:16:04.961 --> 1:16:06.961
And I have a job
to get back to.

1:16:06.963 --> 1:16:08.796
I've arranged for
constable mcginty to escort you

1:16:08.798 --> 1:16:10.631
Back to coal valley
when you're ready to return.

1:16:10.633 --> 1:16:12.533
That's very kind of you.

1:16:12.535 --> 1:16:14.468
It was very nice
meeting you, sir.

1:16:14.470 --> 1:16:16.871
Likewise.

1:16:16.873 --> 1:16:18.839
Miss thatcher.

1:16:20.943 --> 1:16:23.344
[â™ª]

1:16:39.795 --> 1:16:41.829
-Oh!
-I'm so sorry.

1:16:41.831 --> 1:16:43.064
No, no, thank you.
I've got it.

1:16:44.333 --> 1:16:46.233
-Mr. Coulter?
-Mm-hmm.

1:16:46.235 --> 1:16:48.002
May I say it's a great thing
you're doing,

1:16:48.004 --> 1:16:49.403
Building that saw mill?

1:16:49.405 --> 1:16:51.806
It'll make such a difference
for the people in this town,

1:16:51.808 --> 1:16:53.240
Now that
that mine is closed.

1:16:53.242 --> 1:16:55.176
Making a difference is what
life is all about, isn't it?

1:16:55.178 --> 1:16:56.744
Indeed, it is.

1:16:56.746 --> 1:16:57.979
Good day.

1:16:59.247 --> 1:17:01.882
[â™ª]

1:17:10.192 --> 1:17:12.393
[â™ª]

1:17:16.231 --> 1:17:18.065
Ladies and gentlemen...

1:17:18.067 --> 1:17:20.434
Friends...

1:17:20.436 --> 1:17:22.670
You gave us

1:17:22.672 --> 1:17:24.572
Many wonderful suggestions!

1:17:24.574 --> 1:17:27.174
But in the end,
there can be only one.

1:17:27.176 --> 1:17:30.378
I give you...

1:17:30.380 --> 1:17:32.513
The new name of our town--

1:17:32.515 --> 1:17:34.181
[whoosh]

1:17:34.183 --> 1:17:35.983
[applauding]

1:17:39.621 --> 1:17:41.689
[â™ª]

1:17:42.858 --> 1:17:45.126
[indistinct exchanges]

1:17:47.362 --> 1:17:50.064
Well, it looks like
change is in the air.

1:17:50.066 --> 1:17:52.767
It seems so.

1:17:52.769 --> 1:17:55.302
I understand you're
opening a saw mill.

1:17:55.304 --> 1:17:57.571
Yes. Yes, I am.

1:17:57.573 --> 1:18:00.741
It's quite
an ambitious project.

1:18:00.743 --> 1:18:02.810
I do like a challenge.

1:18:02.812 --> 1:18:05.579
The last fella
who tried building one

1:18:05.581 --> 1:18:07.982
Went belly-up
in six months.

1:18:07.984 --> 1:18:10.584
Well, that's not
gonna happen this time.

1:18:10.586 --> 1:18:13.387
No. Not if
you do it right.

1:18:13.389 --> 1:18:15.823
That's the only way
I do things, mr. Gowen.

1:18:15.825 --> 1:18:16.957
[gowen chuckles]

1:18:16.959 --> 1:18:18.959
Well, I do want
to see you successful,

1:18:18.961 --> 1:18:20.161
Mr. Coulter,

1:18:20.163 --> 1:18:23.297
And I may be able
to help you with that.

1:18:23.299 --> 1:18:25.833
Really?
And how is that?

1:18:25.835 --> 1:18:28.836
Well, I know a lot
about this town.

1:18:30.072 --> 1:18:32.940
My expertise may be
of assistance to you.

1:18:32.942 --> 1:18:35.309
Hmm. With
the mine closing,

1:18:35.311 --> 1:18:37.645
I just assumed
you'd be moving on.

1:18:37.647 --> 1:18:39.847
No, no.
I won't be leaving.

1:18:39.849 --> 1:18:42.416
Huh. Aren't you
out of a job?

1:18:42.418 --> 1:18:44.518
Well, there'll
be plenty

1:18:44.520 --> 1:18:46.921
Of new opportunities
here in hope valley,

1:18:46.923 --> 1:18:48.489
And I plan on
taking advantage

1:18:48.491 --> 1:18:50.357
Of every one of 'em.

1:18:50.359 --> 1:18:51.826
Fair enough.

1:18:51.828 --> 1:18:54.261
Let me
think about it.

1:18:54.263 --> 1:18:56.130
Of course.
Take your time.

1:18:56.132 --> 1:18:58.432
I'll be here.

1:18:58.434 --> 1:19:00.868
[â™ª]

1:19:08.276 --> 1:19:09.977
So, did julie thatcher

1:19:09.979 --> 1:19:11.712
Say anything
about me last night?

1:19:11.714 --> 1:19:13.114
Not a word.

1:19:13.116 --> 1:19:14.882
Oh, she talked about
me all night, didn't she?

1:19:14.884 --> 1:19:17.551
No. And stay
away from her.

1:19:17.553 --> 1:19:19.687
From all of them.

1:19:19.689 --> 1:19:21.322
Something happen
between you

1:19:21.324 --> 1:19:23.524
And the princess
elizabeth last night?

1:19:23.526 --> 1:19:25.392
It's none
of your concern.

1:19:25.394 --> 1:19:27.661
Well, if we have nothing
left to talk about,

1:19:27.663 --> 1:19:28.696
I'll be on my way then.

1:19:28.698 --> 1:19:30.631
There's plenty
to talk about.

1:19:30.633 --> 1:19:32.833
I want you to come
to coal valley.

1:19:32.835 --> 1:19:35.002
[snickers]
not on your life.

1:19:35.004 --> 1:19:36.036
Hear me out. Listen.

1:19:36.038 --> 1:19:37.872
I can get you steady work there,

1:19:37.874 --> 1:19:39.306
And it'll keep you
out of trouble.

1:19:39.308 --> 1:19:40.641
Oh, here we go again.

1:19:40.643 --> 1:19:42.476
I'm just trying to help.

1:19:42.478 --> 1:19:43.744
No, no. You're just trying
to keep me on a short leash.

1:19:43.746 --> 1:19:44.812
Tom.

1:19:44.814 --> 1:19:45.913
I've got my life here.

1:19:45.915 --> 1:19:47.815
You've got your life there.

1:19:47.817 --> 1:19:50.050
Let's leave it
at that.

1:19:50.052 --> 1:19:52.820
See you around, jack.

1:19:52.822 --> 1:19:54.488
Yeah.

1:19:54.490 --> 1:19:56.724
[â™ª]

1:20:15.277 --> 1:20:18.479
I didn't see you
at breakfast this morning.

1:20:19.681 --> 1:20:21.282
I wasn't hungry.

1:20:22.417 --> 1:20:24.118
It's hard
to come home again.

1:20:24.120 --> 1:20:26.187
Isn't it?

1:20:28.356 --> 1:20:31.025
I was young once, too.

1:20:33.962 --> 1:20:36.463
I didn't realize
how much I missed it here.

1:20:37.933 --> 1:20:40.467
And how good it is
to see everyone.

1:20:40.469 --> 1:20:42.036
Even viola.

1:20:42.038 --> 1:20:43.237
Viola?

1:20:43.239 --> 1:20:44.672
Let's not go overboard.

1:20:45.740 --> 1:20:47.174
[laughs]

1:20:48.577 --> 1:20:50.477
[sighing]

1:20:50.479 --> 1:20:53.814
Maybe I was selfish,
leaving home to pursue my dream.

1:20:55.050 --> 1:20:57.151
No one's perfect, my dear.

1:20:58.620 --> 1:21:00.154
And being a little selfish

1:21:00.156 --> 1:21:03.057
Is something
we have to do sometimes,

1:21:03.059 --> 1:21:05.526
In the interest
of self-preservation.

1:21:08.463 --> 1:21:11.565
I'm just not sure
jack understands

1:21:11.567 --> 1:21:13.067
I need to be here right now,

1:21:13.069 --> 1:21:15.202
And that it doesn't change
the way I feel about him.

1:21:16.838 --> 1:21:18.672
Maybe you need to tell him.

1:21:19.774 --> 1:21:22.543
[â™ª]

1:21:26.748 --> 1:21:29.083
[â™ª]

1:21:31.686 --> 1:21:33.320
You sure are busy.

1:21:33.322 --> 1:21:34.588
Do you need
any help?

1:21:34.590 --> 1:21:35.756
Oh! I would love some.

1:21:35.758 --> 1:21:36.790
Where would you
like me?

1:21:36.792 --> 1:21:38.192
Out here,
or in the kitchen?

1:21:38.194 --> 1:21:39.593
Kitchen, please.

1:21:39.595 --> 1:21:41.195
I have to say,
abigail,

1:21:41.197 --> 1:21:43.998
For someone who's
working as hard as you,

1:21:44.000 --> 1:21:45.199
You seem happier
than I've seen you

1:21:45.201 --> 1:21:46.467
In a long time.

1:21:46.469 --> 1:21:48.202
Well, when
business is good...

1:21:48.204 --> 1:21:50.971
Oh, I don't think
it is just the cafe.

1:21:50.973 --> 1:21:54.308
I've seen how you
and that handsome mr. Avery

1:21:54.310 --> 1:21:56.310
Look at each other.

1:21:56.312 --> 1:21:58.646
I say good for you.

1:21:58.648 --> 1:22:00.014
You deserve it.

1:22:00.016 --> 1:22:03.717
So does everyone else
in the town.

1:22:03.719 --> 1:22:06.487
It's time for the sadness
of the past to be over,

1:22:06.489 --> 1:22:08.055
Once and for all.

1:22:09.357 --> 1:22:12.126
I couldn't have
said it better myself.

1:22:13.962 --> 1:22:16.096
[â™ª]

1:22:20.969 --> 1:22:23.404
[station bustle and din]

1:22:24.839 --> 1:22:27.441
[conductor]:
Last train!

1:22:31.179 --> 1:22:33.213
[â™ª]

1:22:36.885 --> 1:22:38.886
Jack! Jack!

1:22:40.488 --> 1:22:42.189
-Jack!
-Elizabeth?

1:22:42.191 --> 1:22:43.924
What are
you doing here?

1:22:45.226 --> 1:22:47.494
We didn't have a chance
to say a proper goodbye.

1:22:47.496 --> 1:22:49.029
[laughs]

1:22:49.031 --> 1:22:50.664
It really wasn't
necessary for you--

1:22:50.666 --> 1:22:52.333
-Yes, it was.
-...To come all this--

1:22:52.335 --> 1:22:56.737
I don't know what went wrong
between us last night,

1:22:56.739 --> 1:22:58.872
But I don't want us
to part like that.

1:22:58.874 --> 1:22:59.840
Well, nothing went wrong.

1:22:59.842 --> 1:23:01.875
I just...

1:23:01.877 --> 1:23:03.043
Need to get back.

1:23:03.045 --> 1:23:05.412
I know you do, but...

1:23:05.414 --> 1:23:07.381
[conductor]: All aboard!

1:23:07.383 --> 1:23:09.883
That's my train.

1:23:09.885 --> 1:23:12.219
I'm sorry.
I-I have to go.

1:23:12.221 --> 1:23:13.287
Then...

1:23:15.023 --> 1:23:16.623
Then take this with you.

1:23:19.027 --> 1:23:21.295
[â™ª]

1:23:33.041 --> 1:23:34.975
[â™ª]
